SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: ABR Wave I, Absolute Latency;Auditory Brainstem Response Wave I, Absolute Latency
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A measurement of the absolute latency of the auditory brainstem response wave I of the auditory evoked potential waveform.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Auditory Brainstem Response Wave I, Absolute Latency

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: ABR Wave V, Absolute Latency;Auditory Brainstem Response Wave V, Absolute Latency
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A measurement of the absolute latency of the auditory brainstem response wave V of the auditory evoked potential waveform.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Auditory Brainstem Response Wave V, Absolute Latency

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: ABR Wave V, Amplitude;Auditory Brainstem Response Wave V, Amplitude
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A measurement of the magnitude, or height, of the auditory brainstem response wave V of the auditory evoked potential waveform.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Auditory Brainstem Response Wave V, Amplitude

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: ABR Wave V, Presence;Auditory Brainstem Response Wave V, Presence
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An assessment of the presence of the auditory brainstem response wave V of the auditory evoked potential waveform.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Auditory Brainstem Response Wave V, Presence

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: The volume of blood per unit time passing through a specified location, such as a point in a blood vessel or an entire organ.
A measurement of change in volume of an organ or anatomical feature as determined by a shift in tissue boundary over time.
A measurement of the free choline plus glycerophosphorylcholine (GCP) plus phosphorylcholine (PCh) in a biological specimen.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Free Choline and Glycerophosphorylcholine and Phosphorylcholine Measurement

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A measurement of the creatine plus phosphocreatine in a biological specimen.
A measurement of the glutamate and glutamine in a biological specimen.
A measurement of the glycerophosphorylcholine (GPC) plus phosphorylcholine (PC) in a biological specimen.
A measurement of the myo-inositol in a biological specimen.
A measurement of the N-acetyl aspartate in a biological specimen.
The length of time of N1 sleep.
A relative measurement (percentage) of the N1 sleep time to total sleep time.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: N1 Sleep to Total Sleep Time Ratio Measurement

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An assessment of the latency of the N145 or N2 wave of the visual evoked potential assessment waveform.
The length of time of N2 sleep.
A relative measurement (percentage) of the N2 sleep time to total sleep time.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: N2 Sleep to Total Sleep Time Ratio Measurement

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: The length of time of N3 sleep.
A relative measurement (percentage) of the N3 sleep time to total sleep time.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: N3 Sleep to Total Sleep Time Ratio Measurement

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An assessment of the latency of the N75 or N1 wave of the visual evoked potential assessment waveform.
A measurement of the N-acetylaspartate plus N-acetyl-aspartylglutamate in a biological specimen.
The magnitude, or height, of the P100 wave of the visual evoked potential assessment waveform. This assessment calculates the height from the N75 negative peak to the P100 positive peak.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: N75 to P100 Peak to Peak Amplitude

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: An assessment of the latency of the P100 or P1 wave of the visual evoked potential assessment waveform.
A measurement of the time interval between a stimulus and the maximal response.
The maximum height change between the wave and the equilibrium point of a stimulus-response waveform.
The total amount of time an individual spends in rapid eye movement (REM) sleep.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Rapid Eye Movement Sleep Phase Duration

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: The time between the onset of sleep and the onset of the first rapid eye movement (REM) cycle.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Rapid Eye Movement Sleep Phase Latency

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A relative measurement (percentage) of the rapid eye movement (REM) sleep time to total sleep time.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: REM to Total Sleep Time Ratio Measurement

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: The degree to which the skin can conduct electricity.
A relative measurement (percentage) of the total sleep time (N1 sleep + N2 sleep + N3 sleep + REM sleep) to the total time spent in bed.
The duration of time between when the lights are turned off and when the individual falls asleep.
The ratio between the uptake or binding of a radiopharmaceutical agent in an anatomical region of interest and a context-defined reference anatomical region.
The ratio between the tissue radioactivity concentration at a point in time C(T) and the injected dose of radioactivity per kilogram of the patient's body weight.
The dimension between two surfaces of an object, usually the smallest dimension as opposed to the width or the length.
The total amount of sleep time from sleep onset to sleep offset, determined by summing the N1 sleep, N2 sleep, N3 sleep, and REM sleep durations.
A measurement of the volume of a biological specimen.

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Awake After Sleep Onset;Wake After Sleep Onset;Wake Time After Sleep Onset
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A measurement of the sum of durations of wakefulness episodes throughout the night, not including the wakefulness before sleep onset.
